r/2004915|title=\u2018\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24\u2019 \uc11c\uc720\ub9ac \u201c\ucde8\uc9d1\uc545\ud50c \ud669\ub2f9.. \ub0b4\uac00 \ub354 \ub3c8 \ub9ce\uc544\u201d|website=TV\ub9ac\ud3ec\ud2b8|language=ko|access-date=2019-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828143754/https://www.tvreport.co.kr/2004915|archive-date=August 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|11\n|August 30\n|{{illm|Ham So-won|ko|\ud568\uc18c\uc6d0}}<br />[[Hong Seok-cheon]]\n|\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201908310100249560017327&servicedate=20190830|title=[\uc885\ud569]\"\ub2e4\uc2dc \uc640\ub3c4 \ucee4\ubc0d\uc544\uc6c3\"\u2026'\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24' \ud64d\uc11d\ucc9cX\ud568\uc18c\uc6d0, \uc545\ud50c\uc5d0 '\uc0ac\uc774\ub2e4' \ub300\uc751|date=2019-08-30|website=\uc2a4\ud3ec\uce20\uc870\uc120|language=ko|access-date=2019-09-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|12\n|rowspan=2|September 6\n|rowspan=2|[[Joo Young-hoon]]<br />[[Norazo]]\n|Joo Young-hoon\n|He agreed on the statement saying that he always cause trouble with his reckless comments. He also agreed on another comment telling him to not get back on SNS again after closing his account during a bad situation and open backs when the situation had resolved. \n|rowspan=2|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201909062275782009|title=\u2018\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24\u2019 \ub178\ub77c\uc870, \uc545\ud50c \uc778\uc815\uc655 \ub4f1\uadf9? \u2018\ubcd1\ud48d \uc6d0\ud760\u2019\uae4c\uc9c0 \uc778\uc815|website=\ud55c\uad6d\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2019-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008075231/http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201909062275782009|archive-date=October 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stoo.asiae.co.kr/article.php?aid=57780425382|title='\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24' \uc8fc\uc601\ud6c8 \"\ubb3c\uc758? \uacbd\uc194\ud55c \uc2a4\uce94\ub4e4 \ud0d3\" [TV\ucea1\ucc98]|website=yhnews|language=ko|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://moneys.mt.co.kr/news/mwView.php?no=2019100713128089554|title=\uc8fc\uc601\ud6c8 \uc815\uc2e0\uacfc\uce58\ub8cc \uace0\ubc31 \uff02\uc545\ud50c\ub85c \ud798\ub4e4\uc5c8\ub2e4\uff02 #MoneyS|last=MoneyS|date=2019-10-07|website=moneys.mt.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|Norazo\n|They agreed on the comments that their songs are like endless copies and they are duplicates of each other. They also agreed to the statement that they either took drugs or didn\u2019t take drugs that they should take while working on their songs. Won Heum also agreed that he is like a wallflower.\n|-\n|13\n|September 20\n|[[Ji Sang-ryeol]]<br />[[Chun Myung-hoon]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|14\n|September 27\n|[[Park Ye-eun|Ha:tfelt]]<br />[[Nucksal]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|15\n|October 4\n|{{illm|Kim Soo-yong (comedian)|lt=Kim Soo-yong|ko|\uae40\uc218\uc6a9 (\ud76c\uadf9\uc778)}}<br />[[Park Sung-kwang]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|16\n|October 11\n|[[Alberto Mondi]]<br />{{illm|Park Ki-ryang|ko|\ubc15\uae30\ub7c9 (\uce58\uc5b4\ub9ac\ub354)}}\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/replynight}} {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Night of Hate Comments, The}}\n[[Category:2019 South Korean television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s South Korean television series]]\n[[Category:South Korean variety television programmes]]\n[[Category:South Korean television talk shows]]\n[[Category:Joongang Tongyang Broadcasting Company television programmes]]\n[[Category:Korean-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2019 South Korean television series endings]]\n[[Category:Works about cyberbullying]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|Korean television program}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = The Night of Hate Comments\n| image                = The Night of Hate Comments.jpg\n| caption              = Promotional poster with original hosts<ref>{{cite web|title=The Night of Hate Comments webpage|url=http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/replynight|date=October 14, 2019|website=[[JTBC]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014112815/http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/replynight|archivedate=October 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| show_name_2          = The Night of Vicious Comments,<br>Reply Night\n| native_name          = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24}}\n| genre                = [[Variety show]], [[Talk show]]\n| starring             = {{plainlist|\n* [[Shin Dong-yup (comedian)|Shin Dong-yup]]\n* [[Kim Sook (comedian)|Kim Sook]]\n* [[Kim Jong-min]]\n* [[Sulli]]}}\n| country              = South Korea\n| language             = Korean\n| director             = Lee Na-ra<br>Jeong Jae-hoon<br>Chu Mi-rye\n| num_episodes         = 16\n| runtime              = 60 minutes\n| company              = \n| distributor          = [[JTBC]]\n| network              = [[JTBC#Subsidiaries|JTBC2]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| first_aired          = {{start date|2019|6|21}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|2019|10|11}}\n| website              = http://tv.jtbc.joins.com/replynight\n}}\n\n'''''The Night of Hate Comments''''' ({{ko-hhrm|\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24}}), also called '''''The Night of Vicious Comments''''' or '''''Reply Night''''', was a South Korean variety program on [[JTBC#Subsidiaries|JTBC2]] which first aired on June 21, 2019. Through the sixteenth episode, the show's inaugural four hosts, [[Shin Dong-yup (comedian)|Shin Dong-yup]], [[Kim Sook (comedian)|Kim Sook]], [[Kim Jong-min]] and [[Sulli]] welcomed celebrity guest(s) each week to discuss their reactions to hateful comments, malicious rumors, and [[cyberbullying]] they had encountered online. JTBC called it a new show \"to help the stars become stronger psychologically\". The show also brings up proper internet manners and etiquette.<ref>{{cite web|last=June|first=Hae-myoung|title=Sulli's solo comeback befuddles fans|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/06/732_270821.html|date=June 18, 2019|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620134044/https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/06/732_270821.html|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|last=Yoon|first=So-yeon|title=Sulli cast to co-host JTBC talk show|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3063512|date=May 25, 2019|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610051830/http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3063512|archive-date=June 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Choi|first=Bo-ran|title=\uc2e0\ub3d9\uc5fd\u00b7\uae40\uc219\u00b7\uae40\uc885\ubbfc\u00b7\uc124\ub9ac, \uc545\ud50c\uacfc \ub300\uba74\ud55c\ub2e4...\u65b0\uc608\ub2a5 '\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24'(\uacf5\uc2dd)|url=https://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/0117_201905241726140596|date=May 24, 2019|work=[[YTN]]|language=Korean|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525050312/https://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/0117_201905241726140596|archive-date=May 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The program was discontinued following Sulli's death.<ref name=\"nam\">{{cite news|last1=Nam|first1=Ji-eun|title=\uc124\ub9ac \uc5c6\ub294 \u2018\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24\u2019 \uc885\uc601\ud55c\ub2e4|url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/culture/culture_general/914038.html|accessdate=October 21, 2019|work=[[The Hankyoreh]]|date=October 21, 2019|language=ko}}</ref><ref name=\"jang\">{{cite news|last1=Jang|first1=Woo-young|title='\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24', \uacb0\uad6d \uc885\uc601\u2026\"\u6545 \uc124\ub9ac \ube44\ubcf4 \ud6c4 \uc81c\uc791 \uc911\ub2e8 \uacb0\uc815\" [\uc804\ubb38]|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111245304|accessdate=October 21, 2019|work=Osen|date=October 21, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe show's producing director is Lee Na-ra who produced another JTBC variety show, ''LAN Cable Life''.<ref name=\"PD\">{{cite web|title=\uc124\ub9ac, \ub4e4\ub7ec\ubd99\ub294 \uc545\uc131\ub313\uae00\uc5d0 \ub2f5\ud55c\ub2e4\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7'\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24'|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/05/24/2019052402591.html|date=May 24, 2019|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=Korean|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624080743/http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/05/24/2019052402591.html|archive-date=June 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Along with three hosts in their 40s, it was the first long-term hosting role for 25-year-old Sulli and her return to TV work after a number of years.<ref name=\"cast\"/><ref name=\"PD\"/>\n\nThe show's format includes celebrity guests reading and discussing their own [[Social networking service|social media]] comments,<ref name=\"first\">{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Kyeong-young|title=#\uad00\uc885 #\ub178\ube0c\ub77c #\ub9c8\uc57d\u2026'\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24' \uc124\ub9ac \ud5a5\ud55c \uc624\ud574\uc640 \uc9c4\uc2ec\u2192\uc751\uc6d0 ing|url=https://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/1406_201906221548019643|date=June 22, 2019|work=[[YTN]]|language=Korean|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624080743/https://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/1406_201906221548019643|archive-date=June 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and was noted to resemble [[Jimmy Kimmel]]'s ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!#Mean Tweets|Celebrities Read Mean Tweets]]'' by Kang Hae-ryun in the ''[[The Washington Post]]''.<ref name=\"kimmel\">{{cite web|last=Kang|first=Hae-ryun|title=How a K-pop star\u2019s death reveals the truth about our society|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2019/10/15/how-k-pop-stars-death-reveals-truth-about-our-society/|date=October 16, 2019|work=[[The Washington Post]]|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> On the first episode there were no guests and the four hosts set the show's tone, responding to comments about themselves, sometimes acknowledging agreement or disagreement.<ref name=\"first\"/>\n\nOn October 14, 2019, the cast and producers recorded another episode, per a Monday scheduling, unaware of the death of co-host Sulli, which was reported later in the day.<ref name=\"trailers\">{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Young-rok|title=[\uc885\ud569]'\uc545\ud50c\uc758\ubc24' \uc124\ub9ac \uc5c6\uc774 \ub179\ud654\u2192\ucc28\ud6c4 \uacb0\ubc29 \uc720\ub825\u2026\uc608\uace0\ud3b8 \uc774\ubbf8 \uc0ad\uc81c|url=https://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/10/14/2019101402752.html|date=October 14, 2019|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=ko|accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref> Trailers and an upcoming episode were immediately cancelled,<ref name=\"trailers\"/><ref name=\"yonhap\">{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Jung-hyun|title=JTBC2 '\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24', \uc124\ub9ac \ube44\ubcf4\uc5d0 \"18\uc77c \ubcf8\ubc29\uc1a1 \ud734\ubc29\"|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20191015119400005|date=October 15, 2019|work=[[Yonhap]]|language=ko|accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref> followed by an October 21 announcement that the show would not continue.<ref name=\"nam\"/><ref name=\"jang\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nUpon co-host Sulli's death, some viewers said that the show should be abolished due to the mental anguish it appeared to cause the celebrities as they read and discussed the hateful comments directed at them, and questioned whether such comments might have affected Sulli's psychological state prior to her death.<ref name=\"yonhap\"/><ref name=\"culture\">{{cite web|title=\uc124\ub9ac \ube44\ubcf4\uc5d0 \u2018\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24\u2019 \ud3d0\uc9c0 \ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac\u2026\u201c\uac00\ud559\uc801 \ubc29\uc1a1\u201d|url=http://www.donga.com/news/List/article/all/20191015/97878786/2|date=October 15, 2019|work=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]]|language=ko|accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref> But, others said they felt Sulli participated on the show to fight the culture of cyberbullying and admired her for it; and appreciated the show's efforts.<ref name=\"culture\"/>\n\n==Episode list==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Ep.#\n!Date\n!Guest(s)\n!Name(s)\n!Summary\n!Ref.\n|-\n|rowspan=4|1\n|rowspan=4|June 21\n|rowspan=4 {{N/A|No guest}}\n|Shin Dong-yup\n|{{HideH}}There is a comment which says that Shin does not contribute anything to ''Animal Farm'', where animals do all the work and ''[[My Little Old Boy]]'', where mothers do all the work. Hence he is an old guy or \"old fox\" who appears on easy shows; which he disagrees. Another comment mentioned that he always wittily makes inappropriate comments, but he is actually nothing but a successful pervert; which he agrees.\n|rowspan=4|<ref name=\"first\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3651886|title=\uccab\ubc29 '\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24'\u2026\uc124\ub9ac\uac00 \ubc1d\ud78c #\ub9c8\uc57d #\ub178\ube0c\ub77c #\uc545\ud50c\ub7ec \uace0\uc18c(\uc885\ud569)|date=2019-06-21|website=\ub274\uc2a41|language=ko|access-date=2019-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811150620/http://news1.kr/articles/?3651886|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15609934031465999019|title='\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24' \uc124\ub9ac \"\ub0b4 \ud788\ud2b8\uc791 \uc778\uc2a4\ud0c0\uadf8\ub7a8? '\uad00\uc885' \uc778\uc815\"|date=2019-06-20|website=tvdaily.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2019-09-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chuksannews.co.kr/news/article.html?no=184495|title=\u2018\uc545\ud50c\uc758\ubc24\u2019 \uc774\ub0a0 \uc2e0\ub3d9\uc5fd \uae40\uc219 \uae40\uc885\ubbfc \uc124\ub9ac\ub294...|last=\uc8fc\ub2e4\uc601|date=2019-06-25|website=www.chuksannews.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2019-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906062315/http://www.chuksannews.co.kr/news/article.html%3Fno%3D184495|archive-date=September 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.joongboo.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=1362662|title='\uc545\ud50c\uc758 \ubc24' \